
Step 1. Set up angular client

npm install -g @angular/cli

Step 2. Create a new project

ng new my-app

Step 3. Cloned a repo

jump straight to 
npm install

Step 4. Server the application

cd my-app
ng serve --open --port 8888

Step 5. Import Angular meterial 2

npm install --save @angular/material

Step 6 Verify angular version

ng -v

Step 7 Modify npm start

add file: proxy.conf.json
{
"/api" :{
"target" : "http://localhost:8080",
"secure" : false
        }
}

package.json
start": "ng serve --open --proxy-config proxy.conf.json",

Step 7 install more useful plugins

npm install -g grunt-cli

npm install -g bower

// Test
npm install karma --save-dev
npm install --save-dev jasmine




















